aa(lp338
VPerhaps most exciting to me
p339
aVis an idea that Bill Gates, Howard Buffett and others
p340
aVhave supported boldly,
p341
aVwhich is to ask the question:
p342
aVWhat if, instead of looking at the hungry as victims \u2014
p343
aVand most of them are small farmers
p344
aVwho cannot raise enough food or sell food
p345
aVto even support their own families \u2014
p346
aVwhat if we view them as the solution,
p347
aVas the value chain to fight hunger?
p348
aVWhat if from the women in Africa
p349
aVwho cannot sell any food \u2014
p350
aVthere's no roads, there's no warehouses,
p351
aVthere's not even a tarp to pick the food up with \u2014
p352
aVwhat if we give the enabling environment
p353
aVfor them to provide the food
p354
aVto feed the hungry children elsewhere?
